30/08/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi met with Prime Minister Sali Berisha on Wednesday (August 29th) to discuss political, social and economic issues confronting the country, chiefly reforms necessary for EU and NATO accession. 
Topi's office said the two also talked about ongoing difficulties including the power crisis, water shortages, fires and mine safety.
Separately Wednesday, Interior Minister Bujar Nishani met with police representatives and voiced strong concern over wildfires in the country. 
He urged security officials to investigate the reasons behind them. 
(Shekulli, Kohajone, Panorama - 30/08/07; Balkanweb, Albanian prime minister's website, Top-Channel - 29/08/07)
